  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "REIT Compliance Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Role</strong></p><p>The REIT Compliance professional is responsible for ensuring the organization’s ongoing compliance with all regulatory, tax, and operational requirements applicable to Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs). This is a new role due to their acquisition, and you will oversee all Compliance matters for their new REITs business.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Monitor and ensure compliance with REIT qualification requirements under the Internal Revenue Code, including income, asset, distribution, and ownership tests</li><li>Prepare, review, and maintain REIT compliance testing and supporting documentation on a quarterly and annual basis</li><li>Ensure that all Compliance policies and Investments are in line with MAS regulations</li><li>Support REIT structuring, acquisitions, dispositions, financings, and other transactions from a compliance perspective</li><li>Oversee shareholder ownership tracking and compliance with REIT ownership limitations</li><li>Assist with preparation of REIT-related disclosures for SEC filings and investor communications</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Economics, Engineering, Mathematics, or a related field</li><li>At least 3 years in a REIT Compliance role</li><li>Strong understanding of MAS regulations</li><li>Ability to work independently</li></ul><p></p><p>EA Personnel No. R1985201<br />BeathChapman Pte Ltd<br />Licence No. 16S8112</p>",
